Surface Streets: Geometry and Traffic

Step 1: Import

  • Import STRte_BAAQMD_AADT2014, 2016_Updated_Roadways_Mar11_2016, All_Used_Rail_Linesv2_2016 into a SpatialLinesDataFrame named lnk_layer
  • Rename STI_ID, Id, FID_RR to lnk_id
  • Run a couple of quick checks
return_null <- function (...) { warning("Quietly returning NULL"); return(NULL) }
lnk_layer <- 
  project_path("in", layer_name, str_c(LNK_SHP_NAME[[layer_name]], ".zip")) %>%
  ensure(file.exists(.)) %>%
  {
    
    message("Extracting link geometry and traffic estimates from ", .)
    tmp_dir <- tools::file_path_sans_ext(.)
    unzip(., exdir = tmp_dir, junkpaths = TRUE)
    
    sldf <- readOGR(tmp_dir, layer = LNK_SHP_NAME[[layer_name]])
    
    if_unique <- ensures_that(
      !any(duplicated(.)), 
      fail_with = return_null)
    
    sldf$lnk_id <- 
      sldf@data[[LNK_ID_VAR[[layer_name]]]] %>%
      { if_unique(.) %or% row.names(sldf) } %>%
      str_c("L", .)
    
    if (layer_name == "surface_streets") {
      sldf$MILES <- sldf$Miles
      sldf$Miles <- NULL
    }
    
    sldf %>%
      ensure(!any(duplicated(.$lnk_id))) %>%
      ensure(!any(is.na(.$lnk_id))) %>%
      spChFIDs(.$lnk_id) %>%
      invisible()
    
  }

We add a new attribute, county, that’s a more human-readable county identifier (than CountyFIPS) — county just takes on values "ALA", "CC", etc.

The data in lnk_layer is a bit messy. Because it arrives as a shapefile, it has to contain only one record per feature.

But we’d rather have tidy data, with one observation per row. So we:

  • gather Vol2009, Vol2014, TRVol2009, and TRVol2014 into two columns metric and value;
  • split metric into two columns fleet and year;
  • recode fleet so that TR becomes TRUCK, and blanks become ALL;
  • verify that the 2014 total is (still) 144,491,292 VMT/day; and
  • recode SPDBinID as speed, such that the values 1, 2, … (etc.) become 0-5, 5-10, … (MPH).
stem(sample(lnk_layer$SPDBinID, size = 100), width = 40)

# To find the most frequently occurring value (i.e., the "mode")
most_frequent <- function (x) {
  values <- unique(x)
  values[which.max(tabulate(match(x, values)))]
}

lnk_layer$speed <- 
  lnk_layer$SPDBinID %>% 
  replace_which(. < 1, most_frequent(.)) %>%
  ordered(levels = seq_along(MPH_BINS), labels = MPH_BINS) %>%
  ensure(!any(is.na(.)))
#
# Tidy the data contained in `lnk_layer. Use it to construct a new data frame, 
# `lnk_traffic_data`, that can be used by subsequent steps in the overall build.
#
lnk_traffic_data <- local({
  
  drop_columns_that_are <- function (.data, fun, ...) {
    keep_vars <- names(Filter(isTRUE, sapply(.data, Negate(fun), ...)))
    select_(.data, .dots = as.list(keep_vars))
  }
  
  all_zero <- function (x) all_true(x == 0)
  
  transmuted <- 
    as.tbl(lnk_layer@data) %>%
    drop_columns_that_are(all_zero) %>%
    mutate(county = decode(County_FIP, DST_COUNTY_FIPS)) %>%
    mutate(TRVol2015 = Vol2015 * (TRPct2014 / 100.0)) %>% # "TRPct" means "truck percentage" (county-level)
    select(lnk_id, county, width, speed, Vol2015, TRVol2015, MILES)
  
  gathered_and_split <-
    transmuted %>%
    gather(metric, AADT, matches("Vol[0-9]{4}")) %>%
    separate(metric, into = c("fleet", "year"), sep = "Vol") %>%
    mutate(year = int(year)) %>%
    mutate(fleet = fleet %>% 
             replace_which(. == "", "ALL") %>% 
             replace_which(. == "TR", "TRUCK"))
  
  cleanly_partitioned <-
    gathered_and_split %>%
    spread(fleet, AADT) %>%
    mutate(NON = ALL - TRUCK) %>%
    select(-ALL) %>%
    gather(fleet, AADT, NON, TRUCK) 
  
  cleanly_partitioned %>%
    mutate(VMT = AADT * MILES) %>%
    ensure(all_true(.$year == 2015)) %>%
    ensure(.$VMT %>% sum %>% round(digits = -6) %>% is_approximately(12000000)) %>% # QA/QC check
    select(lnk_id, county, year, fleet, speed, AADT, VMT) %>%
    with_comment("Tidied data from ", LNK_SHP_NAME)
  
    #ensure(sum(filter(., lnk_id == "L0", year == 2009)$AADT) == 81000) %>% # QA/QC check
    #ensure(sum(filter(., lnk_id == "L0", year == 2009)$VMT) == 171473) %>% # QA/QC check

  
})

Next, so that we won’t confuse ourselves with duplicate data, we strip out variables from lnk_layer that we’ve moved into lnk_traffic_data — that is, TRVol20009, etc., along with SPDBinID.

We call the new, stripped-down object lnk_centerlines. It has the same polylines found in the original shapefile, and the same attributes — except for the ones we’ve stripped out.

lnk_geom_vars <- 
  names(lnk_layer) %>%
  select_vars(-matches("Vol"), -SPDBinID)

lnk_centerlines <- 
  lnk_layer[, lnk_geom_vars] %>%
  spChFIDs(.$lnk_id)
SHOULDER_WIDTH <- 2.0 # meters
half <- function (x) x / 2.0

message("Buffering lnk_centerlines by (0.5 * width + SHOULDER_WIDTH) to yield lnk_strips")
## Buffering lnk_centerlines by (0.5 * width + SHOULDER_WIDTH) to yield lnk_strips
lnk_strips <- 
  lnk_centerlines %>% 
  gBuffer(width = half(.$width) + SHOULDER_WIDTH, byid = TRUE) %>%
  gUnionCascaded() %>%
  ensure(proj4string(.) == proj4string(lnk_centerlines))

Finally, we save lnk_traffic_data (the tidied data) and lnk_centerlines (the polylines and un-tidied attributes) together in lnk_traffic.Rda.

write_csv(
  lnk_traffic_data %>% mutate(VMT = round(VMT, digits = 0)), 
  file = build_path(layer_name, prefixed("traffic_volumes.csv")))

saveRDS(
  lnk_centerlines, 
  file = build_path(layer_name, prefixed("link_centerlines.Rds")))

saveRDS(
  lnk_strips, 
  file = build_path(layer_name, prefixed("link_strips.Rds")))

Note that both lnk_centerlines and lnk_traffic_data have a lnk_id attribute/column. That’s by design.

lnk_id is key when you want to roll up some link-level statistic(s) using lnk_traffic_data and visualize them as a map. Here we show how to do that. Specifically, we:

  1. tabulate, for each link, the 2014 AADT for fleets TRUCK and ALL (= TRUCK + NON);
  2. merge these (link-level) results “back” with lnk_centerlines; and
  3. pass the result to leaflet() for a nice map (see help(leaflet) and Google for more).
# Tabulate 2014 AADT for fleets `ALL` and `TRUCK`
# (`ALL` is equal to `TRUCK` + `NON`)
map_data <- 
  lnk_traffic_data %>%
  filter(year == 2015) %>%
  select(-VMT) %>%
  spread(fleet, AADT) %>%
  mutate(ALL = NON + TRUCK) 

# Join to `lnk_centerlines` and reproject to (lon, lat)
map_layer <-
  merge_SpatialDataFrame(lnk_centerlines, map_data, by = "lnk_id") %>%
  reproject(WGS84)

# Render a nice map
leaflet(map_layer) %>%
  addProviderTiles('CartoDB.Positron') %>% 
  addPolylines(weight = ~(ALL / 10000), 
               color = gray(0.3), opacity = 1.0) %>%
  addPolylines(weight = ~(TRUCK / 10000), 
               color = "orange", opacity = 1.0)
